---
description: Inline one-off helpers — prefer long methods over single-use utilities
globs: packages/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Embed single-use utilities

If a helper is called **once**, inline it at the call site. Do not extract a module-level or
private function for a single use — prefer a longer method body instead.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — cwd logic lives where it is used (once)
const dataDir = config.dataDir;
const spawnCwd =
  !dataDir ? undefined
  : dataDir === "~" || dataDir === "~/" ? homedir()
  : dataDir.startsWith("~/") ? path.join(homedir(), dataDir.slice(2))
  : dataDir;

// ❌ BAD — private helper used only once
function resolveSpawnCwd(dataDir: string): string | undefined { … }
cwd: resolveSpawnCwd(config.dataDir),
```

Extract a named function only when it is reused in **two or more** places, or when tests must
mock it independently.
